            <h3>Batangas City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Spend time in Plaza Mabini. The people’s park was designed by the world renowned urban planner, Palafox and Associates. It can be found at the heart of the City just across the City Hall and the Basilica Church.</li>
                <li>2. Pray at the Basilica Minor of Infant Jesus and Immaculate Concepcion. It was built in 1500s and considered as one of the oldest architectural treasures of the city. In the restored Sacristy of the Basilica is the Yatco Museum which show- cases priceless Catholic artifacts.</li>
                <li>3. Marvel the old past at the Pastor-Acosta Ancestral House. One of the several ancestral houses in the City where the original structure and furnishings of old are maintained and preserved.</li>
                <li>4. Learn the City’s history in Museo Puntong Batangan It showcases various artifacts and historical accounts of Batan- gas City dating to the pre-Spanish period.</li>
                <li>5. Dive at Isla Verde. Its dive spots are one of the best in the region. It is part of the center of the center of the world’s marine biodiversity. The whale-shaped island also boasts of long white sand at Mahabang Buhangin with crystal blue waters and thick forested slopes.</li>
            </ol>

