            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>From Manila, it is 112 kilometers with a travel time of two and a half hours. All routes within and outside the city are serviced by bus lines like the ALPS Express, JAM Trans, Supreme Trans, Liner Inc., DLTB Co., Pong and Oning Trans, N. Dela Rosa, Batangas Star Express, RRCG, and Ceres Trans. The city is one and half hours away from the Ninoy Aquino International Airport.</p>
            <p>Ferry boats and other water crafts connect the city to Mind- oro, Romblon, and other nearby ports/islands</p>

            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <p>1. January – The City Fiesta (January 7-16). A week-long celebration starting on January 7 with a fluvial procession where the icon of Sto. Nino, the city’s patron saint, is pa- raded on a decorated banca in Calumpang River.</p>
            <p>2. July – The Sublian Festival (July 12-23). A two-week cel- ebration which features the revival of Batangueño traditions and culminates with the Sublian competition on July 23, the city’s founding anniversary.</p>
